title: Bhogi kundalu muggulu designs by Suneetha || Sankranthi /Pongal kolam || new rangoli
tags: rangoli,rangoli designs,kolam,kolam designs,muggulu,muggulu designs,rangoli with dots,rangoli designs with dots,easy rangoli,easy rangoli designs,rangoli art,rangoli art designs,rangoli kolam,kolam rangoli,kolam with dots,kolam designs with dots,simple kolam,padi kolam,easy kolam,muggulu with dots,muggulu designs with dots,chukkala muggulu,designs with dots,how to draw,latest rangoli,indian rangoli,Bhogi kundalu muggulu,Sankranthi,pongal rangoli
description: It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the door steps.There are many benifits of drawing kolam in front of the house.It is auspecious and believes Godess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.Kolam brings lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.Kolam or rangoli is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to next generation.This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts  of South India like Andhra pradesh and Telangana.People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is actually crushed Lime stone powder available at different parts of India.There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya dasami (Dasara).Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu infront of the house in the early morning soon after wake bringsgood fortune to them and their family.People mix rice flour to lime stone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.

This will be given over and above the existing 50% reservation. In this video, I will tell you why I think this new scheme is nothing but a Jumla and a Lollipop to appease voters. The data suggests that more than 90% of general category people are eligible for being ‚ÄòEconomically weak‚Äù and poor according to new criterion (based on my assumptions). So the question arises here, will the real poor people even benefit from this? What is the point of this new reservation? Ironically, people sill have to pay income tax despite being eligible under this category. description: Besan barfi recipe, Besan Til Ki Barfi Recipe, gramflour barfi recipe, besan ki burfi, Ingredients of Til Magad BarfiChickpea Flour - 1 cup (110 gms)Sesame Seeds - 3/4 cup (110 gms)Ghee - 1/2 cup (110 gms)Mawa - 1 cup (200 gms)Sugar - 1.25 cups (200 gms)Almond Flakes - 1/4 cup Green Cardamom Powder - 1 Tsp How to make Til Magad Barfi1- Take ¬æ cup of sesame seeds in a bowl and dry roast them in a pan while continuously stirring them.2- The sesame seeds have expanded and their colour has changed because they have roasted.3-  Grind them in a mixer after cooling them.4-  Melt ¬Ω cup of Ghee in a pan and add 1 cup of chickpea flour to it. 5- Cook the chickpea flour while continuously stirring them on the medium flame.6- Roast until its colour changes and soothing fragrance appears.7- Add 1 cup of crumbled Mawa to it on the low flame.8- Cook again while continuously stirring it for 10 minutes. 9- Add 1.25 cups of powdered sugar and mix them properly.10- Add the ground sesame seeds along with 1 tsp of green cardamom powder to it on the low flame.11- Stir and roast all the ingredients well on the low flame.12- Grease a tray using Ghee to set the Barfi.13- Spread the mixture evenly on the plate.14- Garnish it with almond flakes and press them using a spatula to insert in it.15- Place it beneath the fan or at a cool place to set for an hour.16- Cut the pieces into your desired size.17- Heat the tray while rotating it over the flame.18- Separate the pieces and serve them.Serving:1- Store it in an airtight container inside the refrigerator and consume it for 10-12 days. description: UNEXPECTED WAYS TO REUSE ORDINARY THINGSToothpaste has a lot of unexpected and surprising uses everybody should try! You can use toothpaste as a cleaner, as a beauty product or even cure burns! We have a collection of lifehacks that will ease your life, watch our video and find genius lifehacks! Toothpaste is one of the cheapest and most effective beauty products. You can use toothpaste to combat acne and pimples, to exfoliate nose and make your skin clear. Simply ‚Äúclean‚Äù your nose using a toothbrush and toothpaste. Dry and chapped lips? No problem! Exfoliate them with a toothbrush and toothpaste. Moreover, you can reuse old toothbrush to clean your hairbrush, to clean the potato and even a keyboard. You don‚Äôt need to buy expensive cleaners, use toothpaste to clean almost everything around your home:-Clean the screen of your iPhone -Clean baby bottles with toothpaste to get rid of milk odor-Burnt pan could be a great problem! Clean it with toothpaste and it won‚Äôt take much effort-Use toothpaste to clean dirty iron Check out more jaw-dropping hacks that will change your life: make buttons out of straws, reuse straws to make cosmetics organizer, use straws to decorate a bag.  Keep your cables organized with drinking straws. For this hack, you will need several colorful straws, scissors, and a permanent marker. Sometimes it‚Äôs really hard to park in your garage and we have a perfect idea of how to avoid hitting the wall. Firstly, take note of the approximate location of the vehicle‚Äôs windshield. Find a tennis ball and hang it from a garage ceiling to use as a guide to not hit the wall. description: In this Video, #AmitBhawani shows you the Royole Felxpai - the world's first #FoldableSmartphone from CES 2019. With the foldable/bendable display, the Flexpai can be used as both smartphone and tablet.Amidst the hype of foldable display smartphones between Samsung and Huawei, an American-based Chinese company called Royole has surprisingly launched the world's first foldable display smartphone. The company that makes flexible displays has unveiled the FlexPai foldable display smartphone. It's an Android smartphone that has a 7.8-inch display that folds to act as a phone or tablet, whenever required. Along with the interesting foldable display, the FlexPai also packs in powerful specifications under the hood.It is powered by Qualcomm's new Snapdragon 855 octa-core processor coupled with 6/8GB of RAM and 128/256GB of onboard storage respectively. The FlexPai also features dual cameras ‚Äî 16MP+20MP with an aperture f/1.8. A 3970mAh battery powers foldable FlexPai smartphone and also supports quick charging. It runs on Android 9.0 based Water OS. The phone was launched in China, and the pricing starts at CNY 8,999 for the 6GB variant and CNY 9,998 for the larger 8GB/256GB variant.Royole launches world's first foldable display smartphone ‚Äî the Flex Pai.For more details ‚Äî  https://phoneradar.com/royole-7-8-flexpai-could-be-worlds-first-foldable-phone/Like this Video to Appreciate our Efforts, Subscribe to   https://youtube.com/PhoneRadar for Daily Tech Videos.
